summary:
soft!villanelle season 2 headcanon:
eve is fucking pissed. 
villanelle does not like when eve is mad at her. in fact, she...
body:
soft!villanelle season 2 headcanon:

eve is fucking pissed.

villanelle does not like when eve is mad at her. in fact, she detests it. it makes her feel grimy. like there’s hundreds of little millpede legs crawling under her skin, tapping against her veins, threatening to break out.

it’s her fault eve is angry too. she lost the target. she got an innocent person killed. she doesn’t care that much, but she cares that eve cares. she cares about how eve looks at her. and the hatred, the resentment, a look with which villanelle is so familiar, is smattered across eve’s face.

everyone leaves the office briefing that night, dejected. all of their leads gone. villanelle has to wait for eve to bring her back to her safehouse. and soon it’s just the two of them amidst an expanse of empty desks and pinned up photographs.

eve slams a desk drawer closed. villanelle jumps. “you don’t have to be so loud,” she teases and soon realizes she shouldn’t have because eve proceeds to kick a rolling chair halfway across the room.

villanelle watches with wide eyes as eve storms up to her.

“you’re-“ eve pauses her rage for a second. she pinches her temples. “don’t look at me like that.”

villanelle has no idea what she’s talking about but obliges and glances away.

eve’s fury returns. “no. NO. that’s not what i-don’t do that.” villanelle doesn’t understand and looks back. eve throws her arms into the air. “you’re so fucking selfish. do you see what you’ve done, oksana? do you see? are you proud of yourself?”

villanelle snaps up. oksana. eve seethes, running her fingers through her hair aggressively.

“don’t call me that.” villanelle whispers.

eve either doesn’t hear or ignores her.

“an entire investigation out the window. just because you couldn’t control yourself. i don’t know what i was thinking. bringing you here. im so fucking stupid, and you’re so fucking selfish, oksana—“

villanelle launches into standing position. they’re standing incredibly close. villanelle can see the frustrated creases etched into eve’s forehead. don’t call me that don’t call me that don’t call me that, she thinks. the memory of an odor floats through the air. the stink of max’s blood. a cake. some balloons. the sound of the front door opening when anna walked in.

“don’t call me that.” firmer now.

but eve doesn’t back down. and she certainly doesn’t listen when someone tells her not to do something.

letting a sharp breath out through her nose, eve plants her feet on the ground.

“oksana.”

her vision is entirely filled with anna now. she remembers the dress anna was wearing. her curly mane tied back in a messy bun. she had just come back from school. villanelle was waiting for her with the surprise. anna dropped her bags on the ground. villanelle remembers every item scattered on the hardwood. colored pencils, blue, green, and red. a tape measure. a french textbook. the tupperware she ate out of every day for lunch. psycho psycho psycho. she will never forget the look on anna’s face. it was ugly and twisting like a sea monster rearing its head in the deepest part of the ocean. not angry, disgusted. oksana, anna screams, what have you done?

villanelle opens her eyes, returning to the office, and she has eve pushed up against a wall, elbow at her throat. eve is breathing hard, and villanelle can feel it intermingling with her own.

eve glares at her in defiance. “are you going to kill me now too, oksana?”

she doesn’t know what to say. it’s taking everything in her to not collapse forward into eve. into safety.

villanelle’s lip twitches. “please.” it comes out a lot more broken than she intended.

“please, eve. please. don’t.”

it takes her a second, but eve puts it together. eve knows her better than anyone else. because of that, she knows how to hurt her. tears prick at the corner of her eyes, and she doesn’t want them to. she doesn’t want to let them. she doesn’t—

eve reaches her hand up, out from the loosened grip villanelle holds her in. she brushes a wet drop from her cheek. her hand is rough but warm. like she is. she keeps it there.

“hey. hey. hey.”

the hand moves to the sides of villanelle’s head, tangling in her now messy ponytail. she pulls villanelle’s forehead to hers.

“hey. hey. im-“

eve shudders, and villanelle feels it vibrate through her entire body.

“im sorry.”

villanelle didn’t realize until now that the one tear had turned into an army. she hasn’t cried in so long that she forgot what it felt like. the last time she cried was in the van on the way to prison. she promised she never would again. she would never mean it.

“everyone who calls me that,” she hears herself saying in a shaky voice. anna. nadia. nadia was going to ditch her in that hell hole. they had been through so much together and she was just going to get out and pretend it never happened. move on to a new life. leave. everyone fucking leaves.

“they-“ she can’t finish.

eve brushes a stray piece of hair from her face. “i know,” she murmurs with a low rasp. “i know.”

the office is quiet except for the sounds of their breathing. pushed together against the wall, they are two magnets. opposites yet inexplicably attracted to each other. gravitational forces. asteroids pulled into each other’s orbits.

and in that moment, villanelle knows too.

blog.name: randomkiwibirds
blog.title: Lost In Time
blog.description:
Becca. 24. Denial.

I am currently living in a underground bunker/cave where I have Internet and everything else I could ever want. I post whatever takes my fancy, whether you like it or not. Be careful were you step because my pet Spoiler Beasts roam freely. Also mind the dragons, and other fanciful creatures that guard my lair. All trespassers will be devoured. Fictional Characters have ruined my life. I do not have a heart and I walk alone, because in the end the only person you can rely on is yourself.

In the end we are all Lost in Time

question: 1, 11, 18, and 30?
answer:
1. What was the first fandom you got involved in?

Doctor Who or Murdoch Mysteries. I wasn’t on tumblr then but I got super into the show(s) (oh gosh that was at least nine years ago!) (I found a Murdoch Mysteries forum and eventually plucked up the courage to join!) And they were the shows that got me really wanting to make fan art and such. (also Downton Abbey, but I had a bitter break up with that show so we don’t talk about it)

11. Who is your current OTP?

I don’t have ships. I have an armada. Filled with many different OTP’s that can chose to make a ruckus at any given time! Though usually they sit quietly until I see something that revives the feelings about them that I’ve so carefully tucked away. 

But right now Lucien/Jean from Doctor Blake Mysteries are still pretty raw or Oksana/Eve from Killing Eve (I only watched it a couple weeks ago so my feelings are not very well anchored yet) Also Thomas/Margaret from Murdoch Mysteries - the latest season just concluded and they went through a rough season and gosh darn it RECONCILE YOU DUMB DUMBS! Oh also Matthew/Diana from A Discovery of Witches - I finished the newest book recently and it revived my feelings for these two!

18. What ship have you written the most about?

I had a brief foray into fanfiction when I was completely and utterly obsessed with the Warriors books, back in elementary school. Since then not much. BUT the ship that I think I have created the most fan art/edits for is either Fitzwilliam/Elizabeth - Pride and Prejudice or William/Julia “Jilliam” - Murdoch Mysteries 

30. What inspires you to write?

Music mainly or the characters themselves. Often times quotes/events from the shows or other media spark an idea into me as well to create! (have a tag for quotes that i see here that inspire me so when I’m really stuck I go through and read through those again)  Also reading fanfiction and seeing other people’s edits/fan art can be really inspiring as well.
